So before you even think to start about getting into any of it, be it stocks, crypto, anything. Make sure You know what you are doing. Make sure you learn first & then apply. Make sure you don't let your emotions play it. Make sure you go after the learning & not money. The money will come along. Make sure you put in the right amount of work & not right amount on money. 


Trading/Investing is purely a game of physiology & discipline. The numbers, The data, The learning & The risk management. 


Anyways, If any of you have any questions or maybe thinking where to start or just want to reach out. Feel free to spam the Dms ;)

Greetings from Directorate of Students Welfare,

 

The Manipal University Jaipur has taken decision to call all newly admitted students for physical/hybrid mode of classes.

 

For your kind information:

The online classes of the newly admitted students is going to start from 25th October 2021 onwards. Link and other details of the same will be shared by your department. The same will be available on the website.
The classes in hybrid mode will commence from 15th November 2021 (50% students of a section will attend the physical classes and remaining 50% students will attend the online classes, The students attending the online/offline classes will be alternate and the detail of the same will be communicated by the concerned departments/class coordinators).
The students those who are planning to stay in the hostel are advised to report as per the following schedule:

24/10/2021, 17:51 - +91 82874 06181: *Read only if you are sure about joining MIT Manipal*

Hi guys, I’m Aditya Korde, a first year student at MIT.

I want to make a freshers intro video and only you guys can make it happen! 
So you guys have to record clips answering the questions below and put them in a drive folder(make sure the drive is visible to everyone) and email it to mit.freshersintro@gmail.com

Please rename the drive folder as your name and rename the video clips according to the numbers of questions. For example, after answering the 1st question, rename the video clip as “1”. This process is to be done for all video clips.

Share your Instagram ID also in the email!

  *Questions:*

1. Introduce yourself (your name+your branch+where you’re from)
2. How do you feel after joining MIT?
3. Thoughts on online classes?
4. Thoughts on campus reopening? What have you heard about the campus?
5. Which student projects/clubs do you wish to join?
6. Anything to say for outro? Kuch vichar to conclude the video.

If you know to play any musical instruments or any other skills, feel free to add them too in the video clips!

Only the most entertaining clips will be taken so let’s try and make this video a great one!

08/11/2021, 10:34 - +91 76107 09464: You guys legit need to learn more. 

First thing first, Metaverse isn't a coin(token). It's a term that represents anything but not physical. 
The metaverse consists of many parts, but here are the basic foundations:

The internet — a decentralized network of computers which is not owned by any single entity or government, and does not require the central permission of any such entity to use.

Open standards- for media, including text, images, audio, video, 3D items, 3D scenes and geometry, vectors, sequences, and procedures to generate and combine any of these things. Pixar’s USD and NVIDIA’s MDL are great steps towards interoperability for 3D applications.

Open programming language - standards for any of the above. Such standards include HTML, JavaScript, WebAssembly, WebXR, WebGPU Shader Language, etc.

eXtended Reality (XR) -  hardware such as smart glasses, haptics, and omni treadmills.

Decentralized ledgers and smart contract platforms - (e.g., Blockchains) for transparent, permissionless, and censorship-resistant transactions. Examples include Bitcoin, Ethereum, Flow, and Theta, Binance Smart Chain (BSC), and many others. These form important foundations for the ownership economy that will support the metaverse and make it a viable public good.

Second of all, what's listed on binance are cryptocurrencys that are building projects around/related Metaverse.

1) Only those who have taken two doses of vaccine can travel in rickshaws, taxis, buses, cabs. This means that from now on only those who have been fully vaccinated will have access to public or private vehicles. Travel will not be possible without vaccination.

2) Passengers arriving in Maharashtra are required to provide full vaccination certificate or RT PCR test report 72 hours before departure.
3) Cinema halls, wedding halls, auditoriums can be attended by only 50% of the capacity.

4) A fine of Rs.500 for not wearing a mask
Shopkeeper will be fined Rs 10,000 for not wearing mask in shop, shop owner will be fined Rs 50,000 for not wearing mask in mall
50 thousand fine for violating Covid rules in political meetings and programs.

5) Only 25% attendance allowed to watch India-New Zealand match

6) Failure to wear a mask in a taxi or private vehicle will result in a fine of Rs 500 and the owner of the vehicle will be fined Rs 500.

7) Social distancing should be followed at least 6 feet distance.

8) Strict prohibition on spitting in public places

????????????????
*MARS ROVER MANIPAL RESEARCH*

We at MRM Research come together to push the boundaries of what we know and what is possible. Research experience and publications are highly valued elements of Master’s Applications/Resumés and MRM Research is just the place for you!

We work on cutting edge research beyond the scope of the rover with a practical focus on solving real world problems. We publish our work in Scopus indexed journals and world-class conferences.

*Apply for the following divisions under Research!!*

????????????????????
*AI:*
The MRM Research AI team engages in top of the line, modern research in AI at the highest level with multiple publications in top conferences. We work on diverse Machine Learning and Deep Learning fields such as:
> Computer Vision
> Natural Language Processing
> Reinforcement Learning
> Bayesian Deep Learning
> Autonomous Navigation & Traversal
> Obstacle Avoidance, and much more.

????????
*ELECTRONICS:*
The MRM Research Electronics team works on developing pioneering technologies in the fields of:
> Communication Systems
> Robotics 
> Photonics
> Networking 
> Signal Processing 
> Embedded Systems

17/12/2021, 20:38 - Dupesh MIT: ---EVERYONE---

Just a quick gyan about DCN (Distributive Computing Network) -

It's a scalable network of independent computers which share/pool their resources to do a big task.  

Like we can throw a strong DDOS attack by pooling all our 300 processors.(assuming 1 guy has 4cores, then 300 students = 1200cores??)

With such horsepower we can do some mind-blowing stuff ??.


For now it's just an idea- Will start the work in offline only...
Till then.. fill this form with your laptop specifications.

+I know this can sound crazyy
BUT
think about it???????????????

*TALENT HUNT MITB*
Hello everyone!
There's a slight change in the talent hunt event, as we know the CinA club and it's activities are based on music, dance and drama but since this is our first event we would be happy if you showcase any kind of your talent and not just skills in music, dance and drama. It might be sports, cooking, programming, painting or literally anything you wish to show! We would like to see all of you participating in it. Don't worry if you feel you feel you have nothing to showcase, you can show us whatever you love doing. The time limit(2-3 mins) and other rules remain the same. If you have doubts regarding anything feel free to contact the core members of the club or dm us on instagram(@cina.mitb). You can also mail us at- 
cina.mitb@gmail.com

24/12/2021, 20:57 - Eshan MIT: Greetings,


I am reaching you on the behalf of Potentià- The MUN society of MIT-Bangalore.

We have decided to organise our 1st Edition of MUN in the month of February, To be precise the 5th and 6th of February. 

We are really excited to incorporate with Manipal University Jaipur, Sikkim Manipal Institute of Technology and Manipal Institute of Technology. 


Here are the details of the Model United Nations.

Mode: Online
Date: 5th and 6th of February

Open to: All the scholars of MAHE. (1st, 2nd, 3rd and 4th year), 
Valuation: Absolutely Free.

PFA, the Google form, is to be distributed among the students of MAHE.


This form is just to get confirmation from all the people interested to be a part of MITB MUN.
Delegate’s Official Registration will be issued to all the people who confirm to be a part of MUN, by filling this google form. The delegate’s Registration form will be provided to the confirmed parties in the 1st week of January.

We believe by advancing this form to you, it is outreached to the utmost number of people, so they could take the advantage of participating in MUN and enhance their public speaking and conference skills.


Please feel free to contact us, anytime.




Best Regards,



Eshan

Treasurer

Potentià 

The MUN Club.
